    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at Model Risk Level 5 for the VAD hemolysis prediction use case. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification confirms 95th percentile hemolysis index remains below clinical threshold. Independent peer review completed without unresolved findings. The computational model is accepted as sufficiently credible to support the regulatory submission for the Class III ventricular assist device under the stated operating conditions.",
